race.comment: GOLDEN LOOM (1) caught the eye over 1300m first-up then raced closer and battled on well but was edged out over the mile at Newcastle last start. Has won here at this trip and the timing looks right for a repeat performance. LUMA LIGHT (6) led all the way for an effortless maiden win over 1400m at Kembla recently. Might have some company up front today but she is a lightly raced filly who continues to improve so do not underestimate. EL PASO (2) is in with a chance first-up on the back of two modest lead-up trials. DORADUS (3) disappointed in his last run here in a CL1 over the mile and has been back to the trials since. Looked good there and if he can bounce back to his best form, he's right in this.
